## Standard Markdown Format

### Quick Checklist Section
```markdown
## Quick Checklist

Use this to track which suggestions you've reviewed:

### introduction.tex
- [ ] Lines X-Y: [Brief description of issue type]
- [ ] Lines X-Y: [Brief description]
[Repeat for all items]

### institutional_setting.tex
- [ ] Lines X-Y: [Brief description]
[Continue for all files in reading order]
```

### Detailed Suggestions Section
```markdown
## Detailed Suggestions by File

## introduction.tex

### Lines X-Y (Section name/topic)
**Original:**
```
[Quote 3-8 lines of context showing the pattern]
```

**Issue:** [Primary issue] + [Secondary issues]. Category: [Type]. Specific mechanism: [explain WHY this is problematic].

**Suggested revision:**
```
[Complete revision addressing ALL issues identified]
```

**Why this sounds better:** [Detailed explanation of improvements - what was removed, what was added, how flow improved, why this sounds like a confident expert wrote it]

---

[Repeat for all suggestions]
```

### Summary Section
```markdown
## General Summary Across All Files

### Most Prevalent Patterns:

**[Category 1]:**
- [Pattern with examples from text]
- [Pattern with examples]

**[Category 2]:**
- [Pattern with examples]

### Positive Notes:
- [What's working well]
- [Strong aspects of the writing]

### Overall Assessment:
The writing would benefit most from: [prioritized list of improvements]
```

---

## Quality Checklist

Before finalizing output, verify:

- [ ] Every suggestion includes 3-8 lines of context
- [ ] Every suggestion identifies both primary and secondary issues
- [ ] Every suggestion explains WHY the issue is problematic
- [ ] Every revision addresses ALL identified issues
- [ ] Every suggestion explains HOW the revision improves the writing
- [ ] Files are organized in reading order (not alphabetical)
- [ ] Target item counts are approximately met
- [ ] Quick checklist matches detailed suggestions
- [ ] Summary section synthesizes patterns across files
- [ ] Positive notes are included (not just criticism)
